<br>
So I just got done playing a bit myself, so Ill put up my first impressions.<br>
<br>
First of all, the graphics are top notch.  I have all settings set to max, 32 bit textures, the whole works, and it ran flawlessly.  The &quot;Bullet Timing&quot; is, in short, fucking awesome.  Its escentially the ability to play in slow motion for a short duration (ala slo-mo movie type scene).  I have yet to find one thing, for the most part, that you can't interact with either.  The attention to detail is pretty amazing.  Even the dropping of the clip to the ground when reloading..  Also, the occasional movie-esque death scenes are pretty cool too  (although Im sure I might get annoyed by it after a while)..  Last, but not least, the cinematics and the comic looking &quot;artsy&quot; storyline is truely badass.  VERY cool.<br>
<br>
I have have 2 cons at this point.  First, being the crosshair.  My crosshair is a TINY white dot on the screen.  Makes it really hard to aim.  Also, Im not really accustomed to playing in a 3rd person perspective.  Will take a bit of time to get used too.  My only other minor detail is during some of the cinematics.  It would be much cooler if their mouths actually moved while talking.  Small complaint, but would just make it that much more realistic and immersing.<br>
<br>
I really haven't played much yet, so I can't say if my opinion will be better or worse as I continue through the game, but at this point, its a VERY cool game.  Not your typical shooter at all.  I'd reccomend it. As playing the game almost feels like you are unraveling a movie plot with you playing the lead role.<br>
<br>
(I'm not saying this just cause I like Hak either :).  Its a very nice change of pace compared to the other crap out on the market nowadays.  2 thumbs up so far.) <p><font face="Arial" size="2">-<a href=http://www.afflictionguild.com/profile.php?username=Jaiieq&charactername=Jaiieq>Jaiieq</a>, <a href=http://www.afflictionguild.com>Affliction</a></font></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#575757><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uojuillean.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ojuillean</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 532<br> <font color=#E9D756>(7/27/01 11:06:37 am)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> <BR><img src=http://www.afflictionguild.com/media/users/Ojuillean/Raidfood.jpg height=106, width=125></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Max Payne</span><hr size=1> I may pick up a copy tonight or tommorow - seems the majority of the reviews I've seen on the net have been VERY VERY positive.<br>
